'''2014年南非大選'''是於2014年5月7日在[[南非|南非]]舉行的選舉<ref>{{cite web|title=Statement by His Excellency President Jacob Zuma announcing the date for the fifth general elections in South Africa|url=http://www.gov.za/speeches/view.php?sid=43484|publisher=GCIS|date=7 February 2014|accessdate=7 February 2014|archive-date=2014-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140509070900/http://www.gov.za/speeches/view.php?sid=43484|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Zuma signs election proclamation|url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Zuma-signs-election-proclamation-20140221|accessdate=21 February 2014|newspaper=News24|date=21 February 2014|archive-date=2019-09-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190912022323/https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Zuma-signs-election-proclamation-20140221|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，藉此選出下届國民議會和各省议会議員，間接決定執政權的歸屬及[[南非總統|南非總統]]。这次选举是南非自1994年[[南非種族隔離|種族隔離]]制度结束以来第五次大選。

== 选民登记 ==
[[File:Voter_registration_1.jpg|left]]

在2013年11月9日至10日和2014年2月8日至9日周末，所有投票站开放新选民登记，那些居住在他们的新选区也将重新登记。总共大约有550万人前往投票站登记，其中包括大约230万新选民。注册选民的数量增加到2,530万，占全国3,140万有资格投票权的80.5%<ref>{{Cite news |first=Natasha |last=Marrian |title=About 1-million new voters register ahead of 2014 polls, says IEC |date=12 November 2013 |newspaper=BusinessDay |url=http://www.bdlive.co.za/national/2013/11/12/about-1-million-new-voters-register-ahead-of-2014-polls-says-iec |accessdate=9 December 2013 |archive-date=2013-11-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113050427/http://www.bdlive.co.za/national/2013/11/12/about-1-million-new-voters-register-ahead-of-2014-polls-says-iec |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Millions of youths registered |date=11 February 2014 |newspaper=News24 |url=http://www.news24.com/Elections/News/IEC-Millions-of-youths-registered-20140211 |accessdate=11 February 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140305055922/http://www.news24.com/elections/news/iec-millions-of-youths-registered-20140211 |archive-date=2014-03-05 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|last=Bapela|first=Kate|title=25.3m South Africans registered to vote – IEC|url=http://www.politicsweb.co.za/politicsweb/view/politicsweb/en/page71654?oid=540293&sn=Detail&pid=71616|accessdate=12 February 2014|publisher=Politicsweb|date=11 February 2014|archive-date=2014-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222030327/http://www.politicsweb.co.za/politicsweb/view/politicsweb/en/page71654?oid=540293&sn=Detail&pid=71616|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在1994年大选之后出生的南非人被称为“自由出生”（Born-Free）一代，18岁以上将有资格参加第一次投票<ref>{{cite news|title=ANC risks losing 'born free' voters|url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/ANC-risks-losing-born-free-voters-20130128|accessdate=24 May 2013|newspaper=News24|date=28 January 2013|archive-date=2014-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140306020948/http://www.news24.com/southafrica/news/anc-risks-losing-born-free-voters-20130128|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

2013年11月26日，南非颁布选举修正案，允许海外南非公民参加登记和投票，进行国会选举<ref>{{Cite news |title=Electoral Amendment Act in Force |date=27 November 2013 |newspaper=Sabinet Law |url=http://www.sabinetlaw.co.za/home-affairs/articles/electoral-amendment-act-force |accessdate=9 December 2013 |archive-date=2013-12-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131214003250/http://www.sabinetlaw.co.za/home-affairs/articles/electoral-amendment-act-force |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

